    "summary": "With over six years of experience in the hospitality and service industry, I am passionate about delivering high-quality and customer-oriented solutions. As a Project Coordinator at Gladwell Academy, I manage the planning, execution, and evaluation of training and consulting projects in the DACH region, working with clients from various sectors and backgrounds. I leverage my communication and organization skills, to ensure the projects meet the standards and expectations of both the clients and the company. Previously, I worked as a Recruitment Coordinator and a Breakfast & Event Manager at PPHE Hotel Group, where I gained valuable insights into the operations and human resources of a leading hotel chain. I also completed the You:niversitynext Graduate program, where I developed my leadership, teamwork, and innovation skills. I hold a Master of Arts and a Master of Science in International Hospitality and Service Management. I am motivated by the mission of Gladwell Academy to empower professionals and organizations to achieve their full potential, and I am eager to contribute to their growth and success.",
